Sec. 201.310. COST-SHARE PAYMENTS. (a) The state board shall
make each cost-share assistance payment directly to an eligible
person.
(b) Before making a payment to an eligible person for a soil
and water conservation land improvement measure, the state board may
require certification by the conservation district in which the
measure has been installed to determine if the measure has been
completely installed and satisfies the standards and specifications
established by the state board.
Added by Acts 1993, 73rd Leg., ch. 54, Sec. 2, eff. April 29, 1993.

